Pivot admin styles tests

Let's considere some styles sets :

/table pivot style sets
[ name      | parent style | custom style                                                
| main      |              | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center' 
| decimal   | main         | decimal=2, text-align='right'                               
| currency  | decimal      | unit='$', thousand-separator='\\,'                          
| salary    | currency     | decimal=0, unit='K$'                                        

Here is the pivot setup definition :
/table pivot setup
/inline  
[ pivot Id ] employee.statistics.module |

[ available measures ]  """
  ssn@count, 
  salary@sum, 
  salary@percentile90, 
  salary@average/managedOu.ouId, 
  managedOu.teamCount@sum, 
  %salary@sum/managedOu.teamCount@sum """ |

[ available dimensions ] 
  ssn, salary, managedOu.ouId, managedOu.teamCount  |
/endInline 

_Check global styles :
/sequence 
[ global parent | global custom | global full style ?                                                   | comments                                                                   
|               |               | thousand-separator='\,', decimal-separator='.'                        | --> Default hardcoded in DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle               
|               | unit='X'      | unit='X'                                                              | --> Override default locally                                               
| main          |               | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center'           | --> Override default by setting a paret style set                          
| main          | unit='X'      | unit='X', color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center' | --> Override default by setting a paret style set + adding local attributs 

_Check fields styles wihout any customization
For this first assertions, the global pivot style is not overrided,
that mean that the defaut value is **thousand-separator='\,', decimal-separator='.'**

/sequence  
 [ measure                             | cross items style ?                                                                      | 
 | ssn@count                           | text-align='right', decimal=0, decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,'            |
 | salary@sum                          | text-align='right', decimal=2, decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,', unit='K€' |
 | salary@percentile90                 | text-align='right', decimal=2, decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,', unit='K€' |
